node.text:
Little Flower: FINAL Part (4/4) 

Come, come little flower,
wind of winter has come with shiver, 
come inside by the hearth of fire, 
little flower I hope you'll remember, 
hearth of fire your home forever

Little steps my brave soldier, 
take a breather, my heart's desire, 
little orange bloom ,I'll take us through, 
from day and night and winter breeze, 

Little flower sweet flower, 
the earth is ripe for your grandeur, 
think me not in melancholy, 
in every moment we spent in glee, 
little flower I'm here, always remember, 
this hearth you once called home forever... 

Poem by @nate.wordsmyth
